cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.MM 

This paper is about developing technologies related to end-to-end dialog systems, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of state-of-the-art end-to-end technologies, which suggests that cs.LG (Learning) could also be a relevant sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses audio visual scene aware dialog, which involves multimodal processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of shared datasets, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound).
